      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>James Luther Adams (1901-1994) was a Unitarian parish minister, social activist, journal editor, distinguished scholar, translator and editor of major German theologians, prolific author, and highly respected divinity school professor for more than forty years.  Adams played a pivotal role in the shaping of the discipline of social ethics in the United States. </p><p>The James Luther Adams Foundation is devoted to the promulgation of Adams' work and ideas.  Its two primary projects are the preservation and distribution of <emph render="italic">The Adams Tapes</emph>, a series of films about the church and Nazism, and the maintenance of Adams' intellectual heritage through the James Luther Adams Forum on Religion and Society.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">James Luther Adams Foundation Collection</emph> consists
            primarily of material from the James Luther Adams <emph render="bold">Forum on Religion
               and Society</emph>, including lectures and other material. Material from each forum
            is filed separately. There is also material on <emph render="bold">Other Events</emph>,
            copies of some <emph render="bold">Recordings</emph> made or re-recorded by the
            Foundation and <emph render="bold">Miscellaneous</emph> material related to James Luther
            Adams. </p>
      </scopecontent>
      
